    "date": "2023-08-18T18:50:32Z",
    "text": "Coal Council Certainty Act of 2021\n\nThis bill requires the Department of Energy (DOE) to reinstate the National Coal Council (NCC), which provided DOE with advice and guidance about policies concerning coal until its charter expired in November 2021. The bill permanently extends the NCC's original charter and thus prevents the reinstated council from expiring."
